    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 996.2 Carrera is powered by the 3.6L M96 flat-six featuring VarioCam Plus, delivering a linear power band and exceptional throttle response. The longitudinal G96 6-speed manual transaxle provides precise, short-throw shifts, paired with a chassis that benefits from a factory-spec M030 suspension upgrade and refreshed bushings. Significant mechanical stewardship is evident: the IMS bearing has been addressed with an LN Engineering retrofit, and the rear main seal (RMS) and water pump were replaced during the last clutch service. The cooling system has been pressure-tested, and the AOS (Air Oil Separator) is functioning within spec. While the finish shows minor stone peppering on the frontal clip consistent with high-speed touring, the cylinder bores are clean and the engine exhibits no valvetrain clatter or oil consumption issues. This is a mechanically sound, driver-focused example ready for the apex.",
